  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across 1 200 Latin-hypercube samples spanning viscosity, pump speed, and inlet flow boundary conditions — results are summarised in the UQ campaign report referenced in the validation record narrative. All 13 credibility factors were assessed; 7 achieved levels fall below required levels and 6 factors remain at epistemic-gap status. Decision: Not accepted.",
